I saw the bad reviews but they were mostly just about slow service but I just wanted a coffee and different really care how long it took. What I wasn't expecting, though, was how rude the man working there was. First, it took a literal six minutes for him to make the girl's coffee that was in front of us (we were the only two people in the store) but like I said, I just wanted a coffee and didn't care how long it took. When he was done, he came over to the cashier. I asked for a medium iced coffee with half cream, half sugar and light ice. Gave me a nasty look and said what? I replied, cream and sugar but not as much as a you would normally put in (never had a problem with that phrasing before but it did take six minutes for him to make the girl in front of me's coffee drink, so maybe he is new, I don't know). He then perked up an eyebrow and and rolled his eyes. I guess that was a very complicated order? He scans the coupon for the $1 medium coffee sale after 2 and drops the scanner back in the holder and goes and makes it. He comes back and says you'll find it at the end, which isn't necessarily rude but the tone was and the fact that we were still waiting to actually pay for it made it strange. Long story short, he was very rude and unpleasant. Didn't say anything offensive but he obviously didn't want to be there and acted like we were wasting his time. The actual coffee was very bitter and had no ice in it (it was still cool, though). Just walk half a block down the street and go to Starbucks. Forget a $1 deal, pay three dollars and you'll get much better coffee and more than likely nicer cashiers.
